@startuml save-simulation

skinparam defaultFontName Liberation Sans
skinparam defaultFontSize 10
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam backgroundColor white
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign left

skinparam participant {
  BorderColor #0056A0
  BackgroundColor #D6E8F7
  FontColor #003087
  FontStyle bold
}
skinparam actor {
  BorderColor #8B4513
  BackgroundColor #F5E6D3
  FontColor #8B4513
  FontStyle bold
}
skinparam database {
  BorderColor #5a7a3a
  BackgroundColor #E6F0D8
  FontColor #3a5a1a
}
skinparam note {
  BorderColor #aaaaaa
  BackgroundColor #FFFDE7
  FontSize 9
}

actor       "User"       as user
participant "Frontend"   as frontend
participant "Controller" as ctrl
participant "Service"    as svc
participant "Repository" as repo
database    "PostgreSQL" as db

user     ->  frontend : 1. Configure simulation\n   (matrix, initial vector, steps, name)
frontend ->  ctrl     : 2. POST /v1/simulations\n   Authorization: Bearer <token>

note over ctrl
  3. Validate JWT → resolve user_id
     Parse SimulationCreate:
     - Exactly one of matrix_id / matrix_ids
     - matrix_ids requires ≥ 2 entries
     - n_steps in [1, 1000]
     - initial_vector non-empty
end note

ctrl ->  svc  : 4. service.run(data, user_id)
svc  ->  repo : 5. matrix_repo.get_by_id(matrix_id)
repo ->  db   : 6. SELECT population_matrices
db   --> repo : 7. ORM row
repo --> svc  : 8. PopulationMatrix object

note over svc
  9. Validate vector dimension
     matches matrix dimension
end note

note over svc
  10. Run projection loop (NumPy):
      v(t+1) = A @ v(t)
      Collect history[0..n_steps]
end note

svc  ->  repo : 11. sim_repo.create(\n    user_id, name, matrix_id,\n    initial_vector, n_steps,\n    result_history, stage_names)
repo ->  db   : 12. INSERT INTO simulation_runs
db   --> repo : 13. SimulationRun row
repo --> svc  : 14. ORM object
svc  --> ctrl : 15. SimulationRecord
ctrl --> frontend : 16. 201 Created (simulation JSON)
frontend --> user : 17. Render population dynamics plot\n    Add entry to simulation list

@enduml
